<subSubSection id="BD6959FB5A364B2CDF644335D6BC41AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F88B1E306932EB4A690F12DA5474CBDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="009F8B6EFE6E741D21318D9475B125A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mexico (Chiapas, Guerrero, Oaxaca, Veracruz), Guatemala (Alta Verapaz, Huehuetenango), El Salvador, Honduras, and Nicaragua, in montane rainforest, tropical moist forest, tropical dry forest, oak forest, and pine-oak forest, sometimes on slopes or in disturbed forest, along roadsides or in coffee plantations, often on limestone, 500-1850 m in elevation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3AE43991662DAE6DC0D12339BF86B116" captionStart="Figure 99" captionStartId="F99" captionText="Figure 99. Map of geographic distribution of L. sideroxyloides based on herbarium specimen data." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure99" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480113" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">99</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
